    "recap_headline": "Akron Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AKRON, Ohio -\nTied 2-2 in the bottom of the ninth,\nBrady Bowen\nrecorded his first collegiate home run to lift the Akron Zips to a 3-2 victory over Western Michigan on Sunday.\nBrady led the offense with two hits, one being a home run, and one RBI.\nBlake Bowen\nhit a home run as well, while\nBrody Chrisman\nrecorded one hit and an RBI.\nJosiah Ross\n(1-2) picked up the victory out of the bullpen for Akron (7-9, 1-2). The right-hander went three innings, giving up one run on two hits, allowing one walk and striking out two.\nTrieg Matthews\nalso made an impact on the mound for the Zips, throwing five shutout innings while allowing no hits.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Zips were trailing 1-0 in the second inning when they first put runs on the board.\nBlake Bowen\nput Akron on the board with a leadoff home run off R. Kidd.\nThe Broncos broke the tie and re-took the lead heading into the eighth inning, when the Zips got back on the scoreboard. Akron scored once on an RBI single off the bat of\nBrody Chrisman\n, which evened the score at 2-2.\nThe game remained tied until the bottom of the ninth, when Akron walked it off on\nBrady Bowen's\none-out solo home run off of Wizceb.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Akron's highest scoring inning was the ninth, when it pushed one run across.\n\u00bb The Zips out-hit the Broncos at a 5-2 clip.\n\u00bb\nGabe Mathison\nstole two bases in Sunday's game.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers limited Western Michigan to just 1-for-7 (.143) with runners in scoring position.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers faced 35 Western Michigan hitters in the game, allowing 14 ground balls and eight fly balls while striking out two.\n\u00bb The Zips drew four walks from Western Michigan pitching.\n\u00bb\nBrady Bowen\nled the Zips at the plate, going 2 for 4 with a home run and an RBI.\nWHAT'S NEXT?\nAkron hosts Oakland at Skeeles Field on Wednesday, March 11, for a 2 p.m. start."
